Although some of these stories may not be politically correct, they do bring up some teaching moments about how the world has changed for the better, and what wrong thinking and behavior is.  All in all, love the classics!
This was a great addition to my older cartoons collection.  It took me back to the 1950s and the cartoons used as fillers on some of the children's shows.
I was disappointed that there was only one Bosko cartoon on this disc. And NO Peanut Butter Sandwiches! I had seen the Porky Pig cartoon on TV.

These cartoons were old when my mother was a girl and not made just for children. They would pop up off and on when I was a kid and I enjoyed the novelty of them, most are very funny. Some are just sweet and pretty. Well worth owning.

If you are looking for a time machine then this is a great avenue to take.  If you are looking for a bit of American history you will find it here! If you are looking to laugh your ass off then you will not be disappointed!  The cartoons in this collection are OLD and have been RESTORED; so if you are young and AVITAR is what you are looking for then this is NOT for you!  If you are politically Correct then KEEP MOVING because you will probably need you meds after watching these!  Great Fun and NOT politically Correct!  Did I mention that they were great fun!

I am a fan of early cartoons specially the ones from the 20's,30's and 40's, this product made me very happy and I highly recomend it. The sound and picture are of great quality, a great collectable item. A treasure of american animation.

I luv all these vintage toons, the price was right & they arrived promptly.  Unfortunatley, the seller's description wasn't as forthcoming as it could've been.  Most of these cartoons look like watching an old film, complete w/lines, etc.  A few of them that are color (as indicated by the credits for the particular toon) are in B&W.  I would've still made the purchase if I had this info, as I luv classic animation and it was a great price.  A little more honesty would be appreciated on the description, though.

charming trip down memory lane.  As a person in the latter category, I thoroughly enjoy watching these
early examples of animation.  It's a glimpse into the past.

Some of these are old, some ancient. There were done when cartoons were funny and clever. The animation isn't great, and the stories are simple, but enjoyable. My biggest objection is that at least one (and I suspect others) were done in color but are shown in black and white. Add to that, the transfer is poor quality -some appear to be from vhs and others could have been tv broadcasts that were recorded.

Despite that, it isn't bad, just not great.

Alpha Video/Oldies.com, the maker of this dvd is never known to produce high quality transfers.  However, absent availability from other more capable and better sources, this will do. It's quality you can live if you don't mind transfers that are way under the threshold of being a decent transfer. The cartoons themselves are fun to watch and would have been nice to keep for archival purposes if they were cleaned up to high grade quality. 3 stars, I think is generous.
